[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Also the `start` parameter was moved on to the right.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Return a titlecased version of the value.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] I.e. words will start with uppercase letters, all remaining characters are lowercase.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Serialize an object to a string of JSON, and mark it safe to render in HTML.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] This filter is only for use in HTML documents.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] The returned string is safe to render in HTML documents and `<script>` tags.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] The exception is in HTML attributes that are double quoted; either use single quotes or the `|forceescape` filter.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Strip leading and trailing characters, by default whitespace.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] The length is specified with the first parameter which defaults to `255`.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] If the second parameter is `true` the filter will cut the text at length.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Otherwise it will discard the last word.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] If the text was in fact truncated it will append an ellipsis sign (`"..."`).
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] If you want a different ellipsis sign than `"..."` you can specify it using the third parameter.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Strings that only exceed the length by the tolerance margin given in the fourth parameter will not be truncated.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] The default leeway on newer Jinja versions is 5 and was 0 before but can be reconfigured globally.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Returns a list of unique items from the given iterable.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] The unique items are yielded in the same order as their first occurrence in the iterable passed to the filter.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Quote data for use in a URL path or query using UTF-8.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Basic wrapper around `urllib.parse.quote()` when given a string, or `urllib.parse.urlencode()` for a dict or iterable.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] HTTP servers treat “/” and “%2F” equivalently in paths.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] If you need quoted slashes, use the `|replace("/", "%2F")` filter.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Convert URLs in text into clickable links.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] This may not recognize links in some situations.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Usually, a more comprehensive formatter, such as a Markdown library, is a better choice.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Links with trailing punctuation (periods, commas, closing parentheses) and leading punctuation (opening parentheses) are recognized excluding the punctuation.
[src:jinja-templating/templates-p02] Email addresses that include header fields are not recognized (for example, `mailto:address@example.com?cc=copy@example.com`).
